<p>Is there a way to find the closest parent scope inside a <code>directiv</code>e that is a controller <code>scope</code>?</p>  <p>Use case:<br> <a href="http://plnkr.co/edit/mSeVBIP7X1mBvjEjiKVi?p=preview" rel="nofollow">http://plnkr.co/edit/mSeVBIP7X1mBvjEjiKVi?p=preview</a></p>  <p>The important part is at <code>line 212</code> is the <code>js file</code>.  </p>  <p>The template I render from the directive has <code>scope</code> expressions passed in the <code>directive</code> attribute and I need to link them to the controller <code>scope</code>.   </p>  <p>Because the directive has an isolated scope, I link it to <code>scope.$parent</code> because in this case the parent is the controller.<br> But this might not always be the case, so how can I find the closest parent controller <code>scope</code>. </p>  <p>Can I loop trough the <code>scope</code> checking if it's a controller <code>scope</code>?</p>  <pre><code>var template = angular.element(html); var linkFn = $compile(template); var child = linkFn(scope.$parent); //HERE IS THE PROBLEM $(element).append(child); </code></pre>